 178#if !NET40

 180#endif
 181      public static Task TimeoutAfter( this Task task, TimeSpan timeout, CancellationToken token )
 182      {
 183         if ( task.IsCompleted || timeout == TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds( -1 ) )
 184         {
 185            // The task is done or will never timeout anyway
 186            return task;
 187         }
 188         else if ( timeout == TimeSpan.Zero || token.IsCancellationRequested )
 189         {
 190            // We have already timeouted
 191#if NET45 || NETSTANDARD1_0 || NETSTANDARD1_1
 192            var tsc = new TaskCompletionSource<Boolean>();
 193            tsc.SetException( new TimeoutException() );
 194            return tsc.Task;
 195#else
 196            return TTaskExt.FromException( new TimeoutException() );
 197#endif
 198         }
 199         else
 200         {
 201            return task.TimeoutAfterImpl( timeout, token );
 202         }
 203
 204      }

 206      private static async Task TimeoutAfterImpl( this Task task, TimeSpan timeout, CancellationToken token )
 207      {
 208         using ( var linked = CancellationTokenSource.CreateLinkedTokenSource( token ) )
 209         {
 210
 211            if ( ReferenceEquals( task, await TTaskExt.WhenAny( task, TTaskExt.Delay( timeout, linked.Token ) ) ) )
 212            {
 213               // Task completed before the timeout, cancel timeout (thus disposing of timer)
 214               linked.Cancel();
 215               await task;
 216            }
 217            else
 218            {
 219               throw new TimeoutException();
 220            }
 221         }
 222      }

 299      /// <summary>

 316      {

 343   /// <summary>
 344   /// This is utility class to implement lock-statement-semantics using await keyword.
 345   /// </summary>
 346   public class AsyncLock
 347   {
 348      /// <summary>
 349      /// This struct represents lock usage scope. Acquiring it via <see cref="AsyncLock.LockAsync"/> will take the lock
 350      /// </summary>
 351      public struct LockUseScope : IDisposable
 352      {
 353         private readonly AsyncLock _lock;
 354
 355         internal LockUseScope( AsyncLock theLock )
 356         {
 357            this._lock = ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( theLock ), theLock );
 358         }
 359
 360         /// <summary>

 362         /// </summary>
 363         public void Dispose()
 364         {
 365            this._lock?._semaphore?.Release();
 366         }
 367      }

 369      private readonly SemaphoreSlim _semaphore;
 370      private readonly Task<LockUseScope> _completed;
 371      private readonly Task<LockUseScope?> _completedNullable;

 373
 374      /// <summary>
 375      /// Creates a new instance of <see cref="AsyncLock"/>.
 376      /// </summary>

 378      {
 379         this._semaphore = new SemaphoreSlim( 1, 1 );
 380         this._completed = TTaskExt.FromResult( new LockUseScope( this ) );
 381         this._completedNullable = TTaskExt.FromResult<LockUseScope?>( new LockUseScope( this ) );
 382         this._notCompletedNullable = TTaskExt.FromResult<LockUseScope?>( null );
 383      }

 25   /// <summary>
 26   /// This interface represents a pool of strings, which have been deserialized from some binary data.
 27   /// The pool stores the deserialized strings, and if on next call the deserialization would lead to allocating string
 28   /// Implementations in this assembly are optimized to perform with absolute minimum heap allocation, causing new heap
 29   /// </summary>
 30   public interface BinaryStringPool
 31   {
 32      /// <summary>

 34      /// </summary>

 37      /// <param name="count">The amount of bytes to deserialize.</param>
 38      /// <returns>A pooled or newly created string.</returns>

 86   internal struct ArrayInformation : IEquatable<ArrayInformation>
 87   {
 88      // Pre-calculate hash code, since data will never change
 89      private readonly Int32 _hashCode;
 90      private readonly Byte[] _array;
 91      private readonly Int32 _offset;
 92      private readonly Int32 _count;
 93
 94      public ArrayInformation( Byte[] array, Int32 offset, Int32 count )
 95      {
 96         this._array = array;
 97         this._offset = offset;
 98         this._count = count;
 99
 100         // Jon Skeet's answer on http://stackoverflow.com/questions/263400/what-is-the-best-algorithm-for-an-overridden
 101         var hashCode = 17;
 102         var max = offset + count;
 103         for ( var i = offset; i < max; ++i )
 104         {
 105            hashCode = unchecked(hashCode * 23 + array[i]);
 106         }
 107         this._hashCode = hashCode;
 108      }
 109
 110      public override Boolean Equals( Object obj )
 111      {
 112         return obj is ArrayInformation other && this.Equals( other );
 113      }
 114
 115      public override Int32 GetHashCode()
 116      {
 117         return this._hashCode;
 118      }
 119
 120      public Boolean Equals( ArrayInformation other )
 121      {
 122         var retVal = this._count == other._count && this._hashCode == other._hashCode;
 123         if ( retVal )
 124         {
 125            var max = this._offset + this._count;
 126            var thisArray = this._array;
 127            var otherArray = other._array;
 128            for ( Int32 i = this._offset, j = other._offset; i < max; ++i, ++j )
 129            {
 130               if ( thisArray[i] != otherArray[j] )
 131               {
 132                  retVal = false;
 133                  break;
 134               }
 135            }
 136         }
 137
 138         return retVal;
 139      }

 157      public String GetString( Byte[] array, Int32 offset, Int32 count )

 26   /// <summary>
 27   /// Provides an easy way to create (equality) comparer based on lambdas.
 28   /// </summary>
 29   public static class ComparerFromFunctions
 30   {
 31      private sealed class EqualityComparerWithFunction<T> : IEqualityComparer<T>, System.Collections.IEqualityComparer
 32      {
 33         private readonly Equality<T> _equalsFunc;
 34         private readonly HashCode<T> _hashCodeFunc;
 35
 36         internal EqualityComparerWithFunction( Equality<T> equalsFunc, HashCode<T> hashCodeFunc )
 37         {
 38            ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( "Equality function", equalsFunc );
 39            ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( "Hash code function", hashCodeFunc );
 40
 41            this._equalsFunc = equalsFunc;
 42            this._hashCodeFunc = hashCodeFunc;
 43         }
 44
 45         #region IEqualityComparer<T> Members
 46
 47         Boolean IEqualityComparer<T>.Equals( T x, T y )
 48         {
 49            return this._equalsFunc( x, y );
 50         }
 51
 52         Int32 IEqualityComparer<T>.GetHashCode( T obj )
 53         {
 54            return this._hashCodeFunc( obj );
 55         }
 56
 57         #endregion
 58
 59         Boolean System.Collections.IEqualityComparer.Equals( Object x, Object y )
 60         {
 61            return this._equalsFunc( (T) x, (T) y );
 62         }
 63
 64         Int32 System.Collections.IEqualityComparer.GetHashCode( Object obj )
 65         {
 66            return this._hashCodeFunc( (T) obj );
 67         }
 68      }

 70      private sealed class ComparerWithFunction<T> : IComparer<T>, System.Collections.IComparer
 71      {
 72         private readonly Comparison<T> _compareFunc;
 73
 74         internal ComparerWithFunction( Comparison<T> compareFunc )
 75         {
 76            ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( "Comparer function", compareFunc );
 77            this._compareFunc = compareFunc;
 78         }
 79
 80         #region IComparer<T> Members
 81
 82         Int32 IComparer<T>.Compare( T x, T y )
 83         {
 84            return this._compareFunc( x, y );
 85         }
 86
 87         #endregion

 89         Int32 System.Collections.IComparer.Compare( Object x, Object y )
 90         {
 91            return this._compareFunc( (T) x, (T) y );
 92         }
 93      }

 95      private sealed class ComparerWithFunctionAndNullStrategy<T> : IComparer<T>, System.Collections.IComparer
 96      {
 97         private readonly Comparison<T> _compareFunc;
 98         private readonly NullSorting _nullSorting;
 99
 100         internal ComparerWithFunctionAndNullStrategy( Comparison<T> compareFunc, NullSorting nullSorting )
 101         {
 102            ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( "Comparer function", compareFunc );
 103            this._compareFunc = compareFunc;
 104            this._nullSorting = nullSorting;
 105         }
 106
 107         #region IComparer<T> Members
 108
 109         Int32 IComparer<T>.Compare( T x, T y )
 110         {
 111            Int32 retVal;
 112            if ( this._nullSorting.CheckForNullValues( x, y, out retVal ) )
 113            {
 114               retVal = this._compareFunc( x, y );
 115            }
 116            return retVal;
 117         }
 118
 119         #endregion
 120
 121         Int32 System.Collections.IComparer.Compare( Object x, Object y )
 122         {
 123            Int32 retVal;
 124            if ( this._nullSorting.CheckForNullValues( x, y, out retVal ) )
 125            {
 126               retVal = this._compareFunc( (T) x, (T) y );
 127            }
 128            return retVal;
 129         }
 130      }

 132      /// <summary>
 133      /// Creates a new <see cref="IEqualityComparer{T}"/> which behaves as <paramref name="equals"/> and <paramref name
 134      /// </summary>
 135      /// <typeparam name="T">The type of objects being compared for equality.</typeparam>
 136      /// <param name="equals">The function for comparing equality for <typeparamref name="T"/>.</param>
 137      /// <param name="hashCode">The function for calculating hash code for <typeparamref name="T"/>.</param>
 138      /// <returns>A new <see cref="IEqualityComparer{T}"/> which behaves as parameters specify.</returns>
 139      /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">If <paramref name="equals"/> or <paramref name="hashCode"/> is <c>null
 140      /// <remarks>The return value can be casted to <see cref="System.Collections.IEqualityComparer"/>.</remarks>
 141      public static IEqualityComparer<T> NewEqualityComparer<T>( Equality<T> equals, HashCode<T> hashCode )
 142      {
 143         return new EqualityComparerWithFunction<T>( equals, hashCode );
 144      }

 146      /// <summary>

 151      /// <returns>A new <see cref="IComparer{T}"/> which behaves as parameters specify.</returns>

 157      }

 159      /// <summary>

 162      /// </summary>

 169      public static IComparer<T> NewComparerWithNullStrategy<T>( Comparison<T> comparison, NullSorting nullSortingStrate
 170      {
 171         return new ComparerWithFunctionAndNullStrategy<T>( comparison, nullSortingStrategy );
 172      }

 174      /// <summary>
 175      /// If <typeparamref name="T"/> is an array, then returns a <see cref="ArrayEqualityComparer{T}.DefaultArrayEquali
 176      /// If <typeparamref name="T"/> is or implements <see cref="IList{T}"/> exactly once, then returns a <see cref="Li
 177      /// If <typeparamref name="T"/> is or implements <see cref="ICollection{T}"/> exactly once, then returns a <see cr
 178      /// Otherwise returns <see cref="EqualityComparer{T}.Default"/>.
 179      /// </summary>
 180      /// <typeparam name="T">The type of items in sequence.</typeparam>
 181      /// <returns>The default equality comparer for array element type, keeping an eye on the fact that <typeparamref n
 182      /// <remarks>
 183      /// Since <see cref="ArrayEqualityComparer{T}.DefaultArrayEqualityComparer"/>, <see cref="ListEqualityComparer{T,U
 184      /// </remarks>
 185      public static IEqualityComparer<T> GetDefaultItemComparerForSomeSequence<T>()
 186      {
 187         var t = typeof( T );
 188         IEqualityComparer<T> retVal;
 189         if ( t.IsArray )
 190         {
 191            retVal = (IEqualityComparer<T>) GetEqualityComparerForArrayElementType( t.GetElementType() );
 192         }
 193         else
 194         {
 195            Type elementType;
 196            var iFaces = t
 197#if NETSTANDARD
 198               .GetTypeInfo().ImplementedInterfaces
 199#else
 200               .GetInterfaces()
 201#endif
 202               ;
 203            if ( iFaces
 204               .Where( iface => iface
 205#if NETSTANDARD
 206               .GetTypeInfo()
 207#endif
 208               .IsGenericType && Equals( iface.GetGenericTypeDefinition(), typeof( IList<> ) ) )
 209               .TryGetSingle( out elementType )
 210               )
 211            {
 212               retVal = (IEqualityComparer<T>) GetEqualityComparerForListElementType( elementType );
 213            }
 214            else if ( iFaces
 215               .Where( iface => iface
 216#if NETSTANDARD
 217               .GetTypeInfo()
 218#endif
 219               .IsGenericType && Equals( iface.GetGenericTypeDefinition(), typeof( ICollection<> ) ) )
 220               .TryGetSingle( out elementType )
 221            )
 222            {
 223               retVal = (IEqualityComparer<T>) GetEqualityComparerForCollectionElementType( elementType );
 224            }
 225            else
 226            {
 227               retVal = EqualityComparer<T>.Default;
 228            }
 229         }
 230         return retVal;
 231      }

 296   /// <summary>
 297   /// This is the enumeration for picking strategy for sorting null values.
 298   /// </summary>
 299   ///
 300   public enum NullSorting
 301   {
 302      /// <summary>
 303      /// This tells to sort <c>null</c> values first.
 304      /// </summary>
 305      NullsFirst,
 306      /// <summary>
 307      /// This tells to sort <c>null</c> values last.
 308      /// </summary>
 309      NullsLast
 310   }
 311}

 313/// <summary>
 314/// This class contains extension methods for types defined in this assembly.
 315/// </summary>
 316public static partial class E_UtilPack
 317{
 318   /// <summary>
 319   /// This is helper method, which checks whether one or both of the given objects are <c>null</c>, and if so, assigns 
 320   /// If neither of the given objects are <c>null</c>, this then returns <c>true</c>.
 321   /// </summary>
 322   /// <param name="nullSortingStrategy">This <see cref="NullSorting"/> strategy.</param>
 323   /// <param name="x">The first argument to comparison.</param>
 324   /// <param name="y">The second argument to comparison.</param>
 325   /// <param name="comparisonResult">This parameter will hold the result of the comparison, if <paramref name="x"/> or 
 326   /// <returns><c>true</c> if <paramref name="x"/> and <paramref name="y"/> are both non-<c>null</c>; <c>false</c> othe
 327   public static Boolean CheckForNullValues( this NullSorting nullSortingStrategy, Object x, Object y, out Int32 compari
 328   {
 329      Boolean retVal;
 0330      if ( x == null )
 331      {
 0332         retVal = false;
 0333         comparisonResult = y == null ? 0 : ( nullSortingStrategy == NullSorting.NullsFirst ? -1 : 1 );
 0334      }
 0335      else if ( y == null )
 336      {
 0337         retVal = false;
 0338         comparisonResult = nullSortingStrategy == NullSorting.NullsFirst ? 1 : -1;
 0339      }
 340      else
 341      {
 0342         retVal = true;
 0343         comparisonResult = 0;
 344      }
 345
 0346      return retVal;
 347
 348   }

 26   /// <summary>
 27   /// This delegate type is alternative for <see cref="EventHandler{TEventArgs}"/>.
 28   /// It differs from the <see cref="EventHandler{TEventArgs}"/> in the following three ways:
 29   /// <list type="bullet">
 30   /// <item><description>The generic argument <typeparamref name="TArgs"/> has <c>in</c> contravariance specification,<
 31   /// <item><description>The generic argument <typeparamref name="TArgs"/> no longer has a inheritance constraint, and<
 32   /// <item><description>The <c>sender</c> parameter of the <see cref="EventHandler{TEventArgs}"/> is missing.</descrip
 33   /// </list>
 34   /// </summary>
 35   /// <typeparameter name="TArgs">The type of the arguments this delegate will receive.</typeparameter>
 36#if INTERNALIZE
 37   internal
 38#else
 39   public
 40#endif
 41
 42      delegate void GenericEventHandler<in TArgs>( TArgs args );
 43}
 44
 45public static partial class E_UtilPack
 46{
 47   /// <summary>
 48   /// Invokes all delegates that this <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>, catching exceptions, and rethrowing if 
 49   /// </summary>
 50   /// <typeparam name="TArgs">The type of event arguments of this <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>.</typeparam>
 51   /// <param name="evt">This <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>, may be <c>null</c>.</param>
 52   /// <param name="args">The argument object to pass to this <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>.</param>
 53   /// <param name="throwExceptions">Whether to rethrow any occurred exceptions.</param>
 54   /// <returns><c>true</c> if invoked any delegates.</returns>
 55   /// <exception cref="AggregateException">If more than one exception occurredm and <paramref name="throwExceptions"/> 
 56#if INTERNALIZE
 57   internal
 58#else
 59   public
 60#endif
 61      static Boolean InvokeAllEventHandlers<TArgs>( this GenericEventHandler<TArgs> evt, TArgs args, Boolean throwExcept
 62   {
 063      LinkedList<Exception> exceptions = null;
 064      var result = evt != null;
 065      if ( result )
 66      {
 067         var invocationList = evt.GetInvocationList();
 068         for ( var i = 0; i < invocationList.Length; ++i )
 69         {
 70            try
 71            {
 072               ( (GenericEventHandler<TArgs>) invocationList[i] )?.Invoke( args );
 073            }
 074            catch ( Exception exc )
 75            {
 076               if ( throwExceptions )
 77               {
 078                  if ( exceptions == null )
 79                  {
 80                     // Just re-throw if this is last handler and first exception
 081                     if ( i == invocationList.Length - 1 )
 82                     {
 083                        throw;
 84                     }
 85                     else
 86                     {
 087                        exceptions = new LinkedList<Exception>();
 88                     }
 89                  }
 090                  exceptions.AddLast( exc );
 91               }
 092            }
 93         }
 94      }
 95
 096      if ( exceptions != null )
 97      {
 098         throw new AggregateException( exceptions.ToArray() );
 99      }
 100
 0101      return result;
 102   }

 104   /// <summary>
 105   /// Invokes all delegates that this <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>, catching exceptions, and passing them a
 106   /// </summary>
 107   /// <typeparam name="TArgs">The type of event arguments of this <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>.</typeparam>
 108   /// <param name="evt">This <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>, may be <c>null</c>.</param>
 109   /// <param name="args">The argument object to pass to this <see cref="GenericEventHandler{TArgs}"/>.</param>
 110   /// <param name="occurredExceptions">The exceptions that occurred. Will always be non-<c>null</c>. Will be empty if n
 111   /// <returns><c>true</c> if invoked any delegates.</returns>
 112#if INTERNALIZE
 113   internal
 114#else
 115   public
 116#endif
 117      static Boolean InvokeAllEventHandlers<TArgs>( this GenericEventHandler<TArgs> evt, TArgs args, out Exception[] occ
 118   {
 0119      LinkedList<Exception> exceptions = null;
 0120      var result = evt != null;
 0121      if ( result )
 122      {
 0123         foreach ( var handler in evt.GetInvocationList() )
 124         {
 125            try
 126            {
 0127               ( (GenericEventHandler<TArgs>) handler )?.Invoke( args );
 0128            }
 0129            catch ( Exception exc )
 130            {
 0131               if ( exceptions == null )
 132               {
 0133                  exceptions = new LinkedList<Exception>();
 134               }
 0135               exceptions.AddLast( exc );
 0136            }
 137         }
 138      }
 0139      if ( exceptions != null )
 140      {
 0141         occurredExceptions = exceptions.ToArray();
 0142      }
 143      else
 144      {
 0145         occurredExceptions = Empty<Exception>.Array;
 146      }
 0147      return result;
 148   }

 63      /// <summary>
 64      /// Gets given integer as enumerable of characters.
 65      /// </summary>
 66      /// <param name="i64">This integer.</param>
 67      /// <returns>Enumerable of characters that are textual representation of this integer.</returns>
 68      public static IEnumerable<Char> AsCharEnumerable( this Int64 i64 )
 69      {
 70         if ( i64 == 0 )
 71         {
 72            yield return '0';
 73         }
 74         else
 75         {
 76            if ( i64 < 0 )
 77            {
 78               yield return '-';
 79               i64 = Math.Abs( i64 );
 80            }
 81
 82            var div = 1;
 83            var original = i64;
 84            while ( ( i64 /= 10 ) > 0 )
 85            {
 86               div *= 10;
 87            }
 88
 89            while ( div > 0 )
 90            {
 91               yield return (Char) ( original / div + '0' );
 92               original %= div;
 93               div /= 10;
 94            }
 95         }
 96      }

 305   /// <summary>

 307   /// </summary>

 309   /// <typeparam name="T2">The type for second possible value.</typeparam>
 310   public struct EitherOr<T1, T2>
 311   {

 313      private readonly T2 _second;
 314
 315      /// <summary>
 316      /// Creates a new instance of <see cref="EitherOr{T1, T2}"/> bound to value of the first type <typeparamref name="
 317      /// </summary>
 318      /// <param name="first">The first value.</param>
 319      public EitherOr( T1 first )

 321         this._first = first;
 322         this._second = default( T2 );
 323         this.IsFirst = true;
 324         this.IsSecond = false;
 325      }

 329      /// </summary>
 330      /// <param name="second">The second value.</param>
 331      public EitherOr( T2 second )
 332      {

 334         this._second = second;
 335         this.IsFirst = false;
 336         this.IsSecond = true;
 337      }

 341      /// </summary>

 343      /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">If this <see cref="EitherOr{T1, T2}"/> is not bound to first type 
 344      public T1 First
 345      {
 346         get
 347         {
 348            if ( !this.IsFirst )
 349            {
 350               throw new InvalidOperationException( "The first value is not accessible" );

 612   /// <summary>
 613   /// This class performs tasks related to objects to "change type", typically on first access (e.g. from <see cref="Nu
 614   /// Furthermore, this class supports the transition which is done asynchronously, unlike <see cref="Lazy{T}"/>.
 615   /// </summary>
 616   /// <typeparam name="T1">The type of the initial value.</typeparam>
 617   /// <typeparam name="T2">The type of the transformed value.</typeparam>
 618   public class Transformable<T1, T2>
 619   {
 620      // TODO this class needs better API (.TryGetOriginal, .TryGetTransformed) and may as well be completely replaced b
 621      internal Object _state;
 622      internal TransitionableState<T1> _originalState;
 623
 624      /// <summary>
 625      /// Creates a new instance of <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> with given original value.
 626      /// </summary>
 627      /// <param name="value">The value of the original type.</param>
 628      public Transformable( T1 value )
 629      {
 630         this._originalState = new TransitionableState<T1>( value );
 631         this._state = this._originalState;
 632      }
 633
 634      /// <summary>
 635      /// Gets the original value, or throws an exception if original value is no longer available.
 636      /// </summary>
 637      /// <value>The original value, or throws an exception if original value is no longer available.</value>
 638      /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">If original value is no longer available, because of asynchronous 
 639      public T1 Original
 640      {
 641         get
 642         {
 643            var state = this._state;
 644
 645            if ( state == null || !ReferenceEquals( state, this._originalState ) )
 646            {
 647               throw new InvalidOperationException( "The original value is not accessible" );
 648            }
 649
 650            return ( (TransitionableState<T1>) state ).Value;
 651         }
 652      }
 653
 654      /// <summary>
 655      /// Gets the transformed value, or throws an exception if transformed value is not available yet.
 656      /// </summary>
 657      /// <value>The transformed value, or throws an exception if transformed value is not available yet.</value>
 658      /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">If transformed value is not yet available.</exception>
 659      public T2 Transformed
 660      {
 661         get
 662         {
 663            var state = this._state;
 664            if ( state == null || ReferenceEquals( state, this._originalState ) )
 665            {
 666               throw new InvalidOperationException( "The transformed value is not accessible" );
 667            }
 668
 669            return ( (TransitionableState<T2>) state ).Value;
 670         }
 671      }
 672
 673      /// <summary>
 674      /// Gets the value indicating whether this <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> is of original value.
 675      /// </summary>
 676      /// <value>The value indicating whether this <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> is of original value.</value>
 677      public Boolean IsOriginal
 678      {
 679         get
 680         {
 681            return ReferenceEquals( this._originalState, this._state );
 682         }
 683      }
 684
 685      /// <summary>
 686      /// Gets the value indicating whether this <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> is of transformed value.
 687      /// </summary>
 688      /// <value>The value indicating whether this <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> is of transformed value.</value>
 689      public Boolean IsTransformed
 690      {
 691         get
 692         {
 693            var curState = this._state;
 694            return !ReferenceEquals( this._originalState, curState ) && curState != null;
 695         }
 696      }
 697
 698      /// <summary>
 699      /// Tries synchronous transition from original value to the transformed value returned by given lambda.
 700      /// </summary>
 701      /// <param name="transitioner">The lambda to return transitioned value.</param>
 702      /// <returns><c>true</c> if transformation from original to the value returned by lambda was successful; <c>false<
 703      public Boolean TryTransition( Func<T1, T2> transitioner )
 704      {
 705         var oldState = this._state;
 706         return ReferenceEquals( oldState, this._originalState )
 707            && ReferenceEquals( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, new TransitionableState<T2>( transitioner(
 708      }
 709
 710      /// <summary>
 711      /// Tries asynchronous transition from original value to the transformed value returned by given asynchronous lamb
 712      /// </summary>
 713      /// <param name="transitioner">The asynchronous lambda to return transitioned value.</param>
 714      /// <returns><c>true</c> if transformation from original to the value returned by lambda was successful; <c>false<
 715      public async System.Threading.Tasks.Task<Boolean> TryTransitionAsync( Func<T1, System.Threading.Tasks.Task<T2>> tr
 716      {
 717         var oldState = this._state;
 718         var captured = ReferenceEquals( oldState, this._originalState )
 719            && ReferenceEquals( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, null, oldState ), oldState );
 720         if ( captured )
 721         {
 722            // We have captured the transition
 723            var completed = false;
 724            try
 725            {
 726               Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, new TransitionableState<T2>( await transitioner( ( (Transit
 727               completed = true;
 728            }
 729            finally
 730            {
 731               if ( !completed )
 732               {
 733                  // Try revert back to old value
 734                  Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, this._originalState, null );
 735               }
 736            }
 737         }
 738
 739         return captured;
 740      }
 741
 742
 743   }

 745   /// <summary>
 746   /// Augments the <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> class with possibility of resetting back to original value.
 747   /// </summary>

 754      /// </summary>
 755      /// <param name="value">The value of the original type.</param>
 756      public ResettableTransformable(
 757         T1 value
 758         )
 759         : base( value )
 760      {
 761      }
 762
 763      /// <summary>
 764      /// Tries to reset the current value back to the original value.
 765      /// </summary>
 766      /// <returns><c>true</c> if reset was successful; <c>false</c> otherwise.</returns>
 767      public Boolean TryReset()
 768      {
 769         var oldState = this._state;
 770         return
 771            !ReferenceEquals( oldState, this._originalState )
 772            && ReferenceEquals( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, this._originalState, oldState ), oldState 
 773      }
 774   }

 779public static partial class E_UtilPack
 780{
 781   private const Int32 NO_TIMEOUT = -1;
 782   private const Int32 DEFAULT_TICK = 50;
 783
 784
 785
 786   /// <summary>
 787   /// Checks whether this <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/> is in middle of asynchronous transition.
 788   /// </summary>
 789   /// <typeparam name="T1">The type of the initial value.</typeparam>
 790   /// <typeparam name="T2">The type of the transformed value.</typeparam>
 791   /// <param name="transformable">This <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/>.</param>
 792   /// <returns><c>true</c> if transformable is in middle of asynchronous transition; <c>false</c> otherwise.</returns>
 793   public static Boolean IsMidTransition<T1, T2>( this Transformable<T1, T2> transformable )
 794   {
 0795      return transformable != null && !transformable.IsOriginal && !transformable.IsTransformed;
 796   }
 797
 798   /// <summary>
 799   /// Helper method to try asynchronous transition, or wait till it is complete, if it is invoked elsewhere.
 800   /// </summary>
 801   /// <typeparam name="T1">The type of the initial value.</typeparam>
 802   /// <typeparam name="T2">The type of the transformed value.</typeparam>
 803   /// <param name="transformable">This <see cref="Transformable{T1, T2}"/>.</param>
 804   /// <param name="transitioner">The lambda to perform transition.</param>
 805   /// <returns>The task to await to.</returns>
 806   public static async System.Threading.Tasks.Task TryTransitionOrWaitAsync<T1, T2>( this Transformable<T1, T2> transfor
 807   {
 0808      if ( transformable.IsOriginal )
 809      {
 0810         await transformable.TryTransitionAsync( transitioner );
 811      }
 812
 0813      if ( transformable.IsMidTransition() )
 814      {
 0815         using ( var mres = new ManualResetEventSlim( false ) )
 816         {
 0817            while ( transformable.IsMidTransition() )
 818            {
 0819               mres.Wait( DEFAULT_TICK );
 820            }
 0821         }
 822      }
 0823   }

 826   /// <summary>

 828   /// </summary>
 829   /// <param name="disposable">The <see cref="IDisposable"/> to call <see cref="IDisposable.Dispose"/> method on. May b
 830#if !NET40
 831   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 832#endif
 833   public static void DisposeSafely( this IDisposable disposable )
 834   {
 0835      if ( disposable != null )
 836      {
 837         try
 838         {
 0839            disposable.Dispose();
 0840         }
 0841         catch
 842         {
 843            // Ignore
 0844         }
 845      }
 0846   }
 847
 848   /// <summary>
 849   /// Disposes the given <paramref name="disposable"/> without leaking any exceptions, but giving out occurred exceptio
 850   /// </summary>
 851   /// <param name="disposable">The <see cref="IDisposable"/> to call <see cref="IDisposable.Dispose"/> method on. May b
 852   /// <param name="exception">Will hold an exception thrown by <see cref="IDisposable.Dispose"/> method, if method is i
 853   /// <returns><c>true</c> if NO exception occurred; <c>false</c> otherwise.</returns>
 854#if !NET40
 855   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 856#endif
 857   public static Boolean DisposeSafely( this IDisposable disposable, out Exception exception )
 858   {
 0859      exception = null;
 0860      if ( disposable != null )
 861      {
 862         try
 863         {
 0864            disposable.Dispose();
 0865         }
 0866         catch ( Exception exc )
 867         {
 0868            exception = exc;
 0869         }
 870      }
 871
 0872      return exception == null;
 873   }

 1009   /// <summary>
 1010   /// Tries to interpret this character as hexadecimal character (0-9, A-F, or a-f), and return the hexadecimal value.
 1011   /// </summary>
 1012   /// <param name="c">This character.</param>
 1013   /// <returns>The hexadecimal value (<c>0  return_value  16</c>), or <c>null</c> if this character is not a hexadeci
 1014#if !NET40
 1015   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 1016#endif
 1017   public static Int32? GetHexadecimalValue( this Char c )
 1018   {
 01019      if ( c >= '0' && c <= '9' )
 1020      {
 1021         // Assume '0'-'9'
 01022         return c - '0';
 1023      }
 01024      else if ( c >= 'A' && c <= 'F' )
 1025      {
 1026         // Assume 'A'-'F'
 01027         return c - '7';
 1028      }
 01029      else if ( c >= 'a' && c <= 'f' )
 1030      {
 1031         // Assume 'a'-'f'
 01032         return c - 'W';
 1033      }
 1034      else
 1035      {
 01036         return null;
 1037      }
 1038   }

 1101   /// <remarks>

 1103   /// </remarks>

 1108   {

 1110   }

 1199#if !NET40
 1200   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 1201#endif
 1202   public static Boolean IsNullable( this Type type, out Type paramType )
 1203   {

 41      /// </summary>
 42      /// <param name="initialSize">The initial size of the array. If this is less than <c>0</c>, then the initial size 
 43      /// <param name="maxLimit">The maximum limit. If this is less than <c>0</c>, then the array may grow indefinetly.<
 44      /// <param name="exponentialResize">Whether to resize array exponentially, that is, do all resizes by doubling arr
 45      public ResizableArray( Int32 initialSize = 0, Int32 maxLimit = -1, Boolean exponentialResize = true )
 46      {
 47         if ( initialSize < 0 )
 48         {
 49            initialSize = 0;
 50         }
 51         this.MaximumSize = maxLimit;
 52         this._currentCapacity = initialSize;
 53         this._array = new T[initialSize];
 54         this.ExponentialResize = exponentialResize;
 55      }
 56
 57      /// <summary>
 58      /// Gets or sets the current array size.
 59      /// If setter gets value smaller than current array size, it does nothing.
 60      /// </summary>
 61      /// <remarks>
 62      /// Setter may grow the array, so that the array reference that the array acquired prior to calling this method ma
 63      /// </remarks>
 64      public Int32 CurrentMaxCapacity
 65      {
 66         get
 67         {
 68            return this._currentCapacity;
 69         }
 70         set
 71         {
 72            var curCap = this._currentCapacity;
 73            if ( value > 0 && curCap < value )
 74            {
 75               this.EnsureArraySize( value, curCap );
 76               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._currentCapacity, value );
 77            }
 78         }
 79      }
 80
 81      /// <summary>
 82      /// Gets or sets the resize strategy for this resizable array.
 83      /// </summary>
 84      /// <value>
 85      /// The resize strategy for this resizable array.
 86      /// </value>
 87      /// <remarks>
 88      /// When this is <c>true</c>, then array is grown by doubling previous length, until it is at least new size.
 89      /// Otherwise, array is grown by resizing array directly to new size.
 90      /// No matter what this value is, the new size will never be greater than <see cref="MaximumSize"/>.
 91      /// </remarks>
 92      public Boolean ExponentialResize
 93      {
 94         get
 95         {
 96            return Convert.ToBoolean( this._exponentialResize );
 97         }
 98         set
 99         {
 100            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._exponentialResize, Convert.ToInt32( value ) );
 101         }
 102      }
 103
 104      /// <summary>
 105      /// Gets the maximum size for this <see cref="ResizableArray{T}"/>, as specified in constructor.
 106      /// </summary>
 107      public Int32 MaximumSize { get; }
 108
 109      /// <summary>
 110      /// Gets the reference to the current array of this <see cref="ResizableArray{T}"/>.
 111      /// </summary>
 112      /// <value>The reference to the current array of this <see cref="ResizableArray{T}"/>.</value>
 113      /// <remarks>
 114      /// Setting <see cref="CurrentMaxCapacity"/> may cause this to return reference to different instance of the array
 115      /// </remarks>
 116      public T[] Array
 117      {
 118         get
 119         {
 120            return this._array;
 121         }
 122      }
 123
 124      private void EnsureArraySize( Int32 size, Int32 currentCapacity )
 125      {
 126         var max = this.MaximumSize;
 127         if ( max < 0 || size <= max )
 128         {
 129            var array = this._array;
 130            if ( array.Length < size )
 131            {
 132               T[] newArray;
 133               if ( Convert.ToBoolean( this._exponentialResize ) )
 134               {
 135                  var newLen = array.Length < 4 ? 2 : array.Length;
 136                  do
 137                  {
 138                     newLen *= 2;
 139                  } while ( newLen < size );
 140                  if ( max >= 0 && newLen > max )
 141                  {
 142                     newLen = max;
 143                  }
 144                  newArray = new T[newLen];
 145               }
 146               else
 147               {
 148                  newArray = new T[size];
 149               }
 150               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._array, newArray );
 151               System.Array.Copy( array, 0, newArray, 0, array.Length );
 152            }
 153         }
 154         else
 155         {
 156            throw new InvalidOperationException( "The wanted size " + size + " exceeds maximum limit of " + max + " for 
 157         }
 158      }
 159
 160   }
 161}

 814   /// <summary>

 816   /// </summary>
 817   /// <param name="array">The byte array.</param>
 818   /// <param name="idx">The index to start. Will be incremented by <paramref name="count"/> when this method finishes.<
 819   /// <param name="count">The amount of zeroes to write.</param>
 820   /// <returns>The <paramref name="array"/>.</returns>
 821#if !NET40
 822   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 823#endif
 824   public static ResizableArray<Byte> ZeroOut( this ResizableArray<Byte> array, ref Int32 idx, Int32 count )
 825   {
 0826      if ( count > 0 )
 827      {
 0828         array.FillWithOffsetAndCount( idx, count, (Byte) 0 );
 0829         idx += count;
 830      }
 0831      return array;
 832   }

 834   /// <summary>
 835   /// This is method to quickly fill array with values, utilizing the fact that <see cref="Array.Copy(Array, Array, Int

 842   /// <exception cref="ArgumentException">If <paramref name="destinationArray"/> is not empty, and length of <paramref

 844   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 845#endif
 846   public static ResizableArray<T> Fill<T>( this ResizableArray<T> destinationArray, params T[] value )

 0848      return destinationArray.FillWithOffsetAndCount( 0, destinationArray.CurrentMaxCapacity, value );

 869   /// </summary>
 870   /// <typeparam name="T">The type of array elements.</typeparam>
 871   /// <param name="destinationArray">The array to be filled with values.</param>

 885   /// <summary>
 886   /// This is method to quickly fill array with values, utilizing the fact that <see cref="Array.Copy(Array, Array, Int
 887   /// </summary>
 888   /// <typeparam name="T">The type of array elements.</typeparam>
 889   /// <param name="destinationArray">The array to be filled with values.</param>
 890   /// <param name="value">The values to fill array with.</param>
 891   /// <param name="offset">The offset at which to start filling array.</param>
 892   /// <param name="count">How many items to fill.</param>
 893   /// <returns>The <paramref name="destinationArray"/></returns>
 894   /// <remarks>
 895   /// Original source code is found at <see href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5943850/fastest-way-to-fill-an-arr
 896   /// According to first link, "<c>In my test with 20,000,000 array items, this function is twice as fast as a for loop
 897   /// The source code was modified to fix a bug and also to support offset and count parameters.
 898   /// </remarks>
 899   /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">If <paramref name="destinationArray"/> or <paramref name="value"/> are nu
 900   /// <exception cref="ArgumentException">If <paramref name="destinationArray"/> is not empty, and length of <paramref 
 901#if !NET40
 902   [System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImpl( System.Runtime.CompilerServices.MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining )]
 903#endif
 904   public static ResizableArray<T> FillWithOffsetAndCount<T>( this ResizableArray<T> destinationArray, Int32 offset, Int
 905   {
 0906      ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( "Destination array", destinationArray );
 0907      if ( offset < 0 )
 908      {
 0909         throw new ArgumentOutOfRangeException( "Offset" );
 910      }
 0911      destinationArray.CurrentMaxCapacity = offset + count;
 912
 0913      if ( count > 0 )
 914      {
 0915         ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotEmpty( "Value array", value );
 916
 0917         var array = destinationArray.Array;
 918
 919
 0920         var max = offset + count;
 0921         if ( value.Length > count )
 922         {
 0923            throw new ArgumentException( "Length of value array must not be more than count in destination" );
 924         }
 925
 926         // set the initial array value
 0927         Array.Copy( value, 0, array, offset, value.Length );
 928
 929         Int32 copyLength;
 930
 0931         for ( copyLength = value.Length; copyLength + copyLength < count; copyLength <<= 1 )
 932         {
 0933            Array.Copy( array, offset, array, offset + copyLength, copyLength );
 934         }
 935
 0936         Array.Copy( array, offset, array, offset + copyLength, count - copyLength );
 937
 938      }
 0939      return destinationArray;
 940   }

 239      public async ValueTask<TValue> TryReadNextAsync()
 240      {
 241         var retVal = await this.Reader.TryReadNextAsync( this.Source );
 242         this.ReadCompleted?.Invoke( new ReadCompletedEventArgsImpl<TValue>( this.Reader.IsReadSuccessful( retVal ), ret
 243         return retVal;
 244      }

 252   /// <summary>
 253   /// This class provides implementation for <see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue}.TryReadNextAsync"/> and <see cre
 254   /// </summary>
 255   public sealed class BoundPeekablePotentiallyAsyncReader<TValue, TSource> : PeekablePotentiallyAsyncReader<TValue>
 256   {
 257      private Boolean _hasPeekedValue;
 258      private TValue _peekedValue;
 259      private Boolean _ended;
 260
 261      /// <summary>
 262      /// Creates a new instance of <see cref="BoundPeekablePotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TSource}"/> with given reader
 263      /// </summary>
 264      /// <param name="reader">The <see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic{TValue, TSource}"/>.</param>
 265      /// <param name="source">The source for <paramref name="reader"/>.</param>
 266      /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">If <paramref name="reader"/> is <c>null</c>.</exception>
 267      internal BoundPeekablePotentiallyAsyncReader(
 268        PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic<TValue, TSource> reader,
 269        TSource source
 270        )
 271      {
 272         this.Reader = ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( reader ), reader );
 273         this.Source = source;
 274      }
 275
 276      /// <summary>
 277      /// Gets the source of this reader.
 278      /// </summary>
 279      /// <value>The source of this reader.</value>
 280      public TSource Source { get; }
 281
 282      /// <summary>
 283      /// Gets the underlying reader.
 284      /// </summary>
 285      /// <value>The underlying reader.</value>
 286      public PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic<TValue, TSource> Reader { get; }
 287
 288      /// <summary>
 289      /// <see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic{TValue, TSource}.TryReadNextAsync"/>.
 290      /// </summary>
 291      /// <returns><see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic{TValue, TSource}.TryReadNextAsync"/>.</returns>
 292      public async ValueTask<TValue> TryReadNextAsync()
 293      {
 294         // TODO Interlocked.CompareExchange(ref this._state ... ) guards
 295         TValue retVal;
 296         Boolean readSuccessful;
 297         if ( this._ended )
 298         {
 299            retVal = this._peekedValue;
 300            readSuccessful = false;
 301         }
 302         else if ( this._hasPeekedValue )
 303         {
 304            retVal = this._peekedValue;
 305            this._hasPeekedValue = false;
 306            readSuccessful = true;
 307         }
 308         else
 309         {
 310            retVal = await this.Reader.TryReadNextAsync( this.Source );
 311            readSuccessful = this.Reader.IsReadSuccessful( retVal );
 312            if ( !readSuccessful )
 313            {
 314               this._ended = true;
 315               this._peekedValue = retVal;
 316            }
 317         }
 318
 319         this.ReadCompleted?.Invoke( new ReadCompletedEventArgsImpl<TValue>( readSuccessful, retVal ) );
 320
 321         return retVal;
 322      }
 323
 324      /// <summary>
 325      /// <see cref="PeekablePotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue}.TryPeekAsync"/>.
 326      /// </summary>
 327      /// <returns><see cref="PeekablePotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue}.TryPeekAsync"/>.</returns>
 328      public async ValueTask<TValue> TryPeekAsync()
 329      {
 330         TValue retVal;
 331         if ( this._ended )
 332         {
 333            retVal = this._peekedValue;
 334         }
 335         else if ( this._hasPeekedValue )
 336         {
 337            retVal = this._peekedValue;
 338         }
 339         else
 340         {
 341            retVal = await this.Reader.TryReadNextAsync( this.Source );
 342            this._peekedValue = retVal;
 343            if ( !this.Reader.IsReadSuccessful( retVal ) )
 344            {
 345               this._ended = true;
 346            }
 347         }
 348
 349         return retVal;
 350      }
 351

 353      /// <see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReaderObservable{TValue}.ReadCompleted"/>.
 354      /// </summary>
 355      public event GenericEventHandler<ReadCompletedEventArgs<TValue>> ReadCompleted;
 356   }

 358   /// <summary>
 359   /// This class implements <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}"/>.
 360   /// </summary>
 361   /// <typeparam name="TValue">The type of values this reader produces.</typeparam>
 362   /// <typeparam name="TBufferItem">The type of buffer items that this reader memorizes.</typeparam>
 363   /// <typeparam name="TSource">The type of source bound to this reader.</typeparam>
 364   public sealed class BoundMemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader<TValue, TBufferItem, TSource> : MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncR
 365   {
 366      private readonly ResizableArray<TBufferItem> _buffer;
 367      private readonly Func<TValue, TBufferItem> _transform;
 368      private readonly Func<TBufferItem, TValue> _transformBack;
 369      private Int32 _bufferSize;
 370      private Int32 _bufferUseable;
 371
 372      internal BoundMemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader(
 373        PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic<TValue, TSource> reader,
 374        TSource source,
 375        ResizableArray<TBufferItem> buffer,
 376        Func<TValue, TBufferItem> transform,
 377        Func<TBufferItem, TValue> transformBack
 378        )
 379      {
 380         this.Reader = ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( reader ), reader );
 381         this.Source = source;
 382         this._buffer = buffer ?? new ResizableArray<TBufferItem>();
 383         this._transform = ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( transform ), transform );
 384         this._transformBack = ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( transformBack ), transformBack );
 385      }
 386
 387      /// <summary>
 388      /// Gets the source of this reader.
 389      /// </summary>
 390      /// <value>The source of this reader.</value>
 391      public TSource Source { get; }
 392
 393      /// <summary>
 394      /// Gets the underlying reader.
 395      /// </summary>
 396      /// <value>The underlying reader.</value>
 397      public PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic<TValue, TSource> Reader { get; }
 398
 399      /// <summary>
 400      /// <see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic{TValue, TSource}.TryReadNextAsync"/>.
 401      /// </summary>
 402      /// <returns><see cref="PotentiallyAsyncReaderLogic{TValue, TSource}.TryReadNextAsync"/>.</returns>
 403      public async ValueTask<TValue> TryReadNextAsync()
 404      {
 405         var success = this._bufferUseable < this._bufferSize;
 406         TValue retVal;
 407         if ( success )
 408         {
 409            retVal = this._transformBack( this._buffer.Array[this._bufferUseable] );
 410            Interlocked.Increment( ref this._bufferUseable );
 411         }
 412         else
 413         {
 414            retVal = await this.Reader.TryReadNextAsync( this.Source );
 415            success = this.Reader.IsReadSuccessful( retVal );
 416            if ( success )
 417            {
 418               var newSize = this._bufferSize + 1;
 419               this._buffer.CurrentMaxCapacity = newSize;
 420               this._buffer.Array[newSize - 1] = this._transform( retVal );
 421               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bufferSize, newSize );
 422               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bufferUseable, newSize );
 423            }
 424         }
 425
 426         this.ReadCompleted?.Invoke( new ReadCompletedEventArgsImpl<TValue>( success, retVal ) );
 427
 428         return retVal;
 429      }
 430
 431      /// <inheritdoc />
 432      public async ValueTask<TValue> TryPeekAsync()
 433      {
 434         TValue retVal;
 435         if ( this._bufferUseable < this._bufferSize )
 436         {
 437            retVal = this._transformBack( this._buffer.Array[this._bufferUseable] );
 438         }
 439         else
 440         {
 441            retVal = await this.Reader.TryReadNextAsync( this.Source );
 442            if ( this.Reader.IsReadSuccessful( retVal ) )
 443            {
 444               var newSize = this._bufferSize + 1;
 445               this._buffer.CurrentMaxCapacity = newSize;
 446               this._buffer.Array[newSize - 1] = this._transform( retVal );
 447               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bufferSize, newSize );
 448            }
 449         }
 450
 451         return retVal;
 452      }
 453
 454      /// <summary>
 455      /// This will become System.Span when it's available.
 456      /// </summary>
 457      /// <value>The current buffer span.</value>
 458      public TBufferItem[] Buffer
 459      {
 460         get
 461         {
 462            return this._buffer.Array;
 463         }
 464      }
 465
 466      /// <summary>
 467      /// Gets the amount of useable items in <see cref="Buffer"/>.
 468      /// </summary>
 469      /// <value>The amount of useable items in <see cref="Buffer"/>.</value>
 470      public Int32 BufferCount
 471      {
 472         get
 473         {
 474            return this._bufferUseable;
 475         }
 476      }
 477
 478      /// <summary>
 479      /// Clears the current buffer.
 480      /// </summary>
 481      public void ClearBuffer()
 482      {
 483         // TODO this is copy-paste from stream reader
 484         if ( this._bufferUseable > 0 && this._bufferUseable <= this._bufferSize )
 485         {
 486            this._buffer.Array.ShiftArraySegmentLeft( ref this._bufferSize, 0, this._bufferUseable );
 487            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bufferUseable, 0 );
 488         }
 489      }
 490
 491      /// <inheritdoc />
 492      public void EraseBufferSegment( Int32 firstDeletableIndex, Int32 count )
 493      {
 494         if ( firstDeletableIndex >= 0 && count > 0 && firstDeletableIndex + count <= this._bufferUseable )
 495         {
 496            this.Buffer.ShiftArraySegmentLeft( ref this._bufferSize, firstDeletableIndex, count );
 497            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bufferUseable, this._bufferUseable - count );
 498         }
 499      }
 500
 501      /// <inheritdoc />
 502      public void ForgetBufferedItems( Int32 amount )
 503      {
 504         if ( amount < 0 )
 505         {
 506            amount = this._bufferUseable;
 507         }
 508
 509         if ( amount > 0 && amount <= this._bufferUseable )
 510         {
 511            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bufferUseable, this._bufferUseable - amount );
 512         }
 513      }

 521   /// <summary>
 522   /// This class represents incrementable index in a string.
 523   /// </summary>
 524   public sealed class StringIndex
 525   {
 526      private Int32 _idx;
 527      private readonly Int32 _max;
 528
 529      /// <summary>
 530      /// Creates a new instance of <see cref="StringIndex"/> with given string and optional range.
 531      /// </summary>
 532      /// <param name="str">The string.</param>
 533      /// <param name="offset">The starting index.</param>
 534      /// <param name="count">The amount of characters to include to be indexed. Negative values are interpreted as "the
 535      /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">If <paramref name="str"/> is <c>null</c>.</exception>
 536      public StringIndex(
 537         String str,
 538         Int32 offset = 0,
 539         Int32 count = -1
 540         )
 541      {
 542         this.String = ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( str ), str );
 543         this._idx = Math.Max( offset, 0 );
 544         if ( count < 0 )
 545         {
 546            count = str.Length - this._idx;
 547         }
 548         this._max = Math.Min( this._idx + count, str.Length );
 549      }
 550
 551      /// <summary>
 552      /// Gets the full string as given to this <see cref="StringIndex"/>.
 553      /// </summary>
 554      /// <value>The full string as given to this <see cref="StringIndex"/>.</value>
 555      public String String { get; }
 556
 557      /// <summary>
 558      /// Gets the current index to the string of this <see cref="StringIndex"/>.
 559      /// </summary>
 560      /// <value>The current index to the string of this <see cref="StringIndex"/>.</value>
 561      public Int32 CurrentIndex
 562      {
 563         get
 564         {
 565            return this._idx;
 566         }
 567      }
 568
 569      /// <summary>
 570      /// Tries to get index for the next character.
 571      /// </summary>
 572      /// <param name="idx">This parameter will hold the index.</param>
 573      /// <returns><c>true</c> if <paramref name="idx"/> will fall within acceptable range; <c>false</c> otherwise.</ret
 574      public Boolean TryGetNextIndex( out Int32 idx )
 575      {
 576         if ( this._idx < this._max && ( idx = Interlocked.Increment( ref this._idx ) ) <= this._max )
 577         {
 578            // Interlocked.Increment returns incremented value
 579            --idx;
 580         }
 581         else
 582         {
 583            idx = this._max;
 584         }
 585
 586         return idx < this._max;
 587      }
 588   }

 677   {

 686      /// <summary>

 706      /// <summary>
 707      /// Tries to read next character from given <paramref name="stream"/>.
 708      /// </summary>
 709      /// <param name="stream">The <see cref="StreamReaderWithResizableBuffer"/> to read character from. The <see cref="
 710      /// <returns>A task which will return character read, or <c>null</c> if no more characters could be read from <par
 711      /// <exception cref="ArgumentNullException">If <paramref name="stream"/> is <c>null</c>.</exception>
 712      /// <exception cref="InvalidOperationException">If this reader is currently busy with another read operation.</exc
 713      public async ValueTask<Char?> TryReadNextAsync(
 714         StreamReaderWithResizableBuffer stream
 715      )
 716      {
 717         ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( stream ), stream );
 718         if ( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, BUSY, IDLE ) == IDLE )
 719         {
 720            try
 721            {
 722               Char? retVal;
 723               Boolean charReadSuccessful;
 724               if ( this._lowSurrogate != 0 )
 725               {
 726                  // We have read surrogate pair previously -> return low surrogate
 727                  retVal = (Char) this._lowSurrogate;
 728                  charReadSuccessful = true;
 729                  Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._lowSurrogate, 0 );
 730               }
 731               else
 732               {
 733                  var decoder = this.Encoding.Encoding.GetDecoder();
 734                  var auxArray = this._chars;
 735                  var minChar = this._minChar;
 736                  var arrayIndex = stream.ReadBytesCount;
 737                  charReadSuccessful = await stream.TryReadMoreAsync( minChar );
 738                  if ( charReadSuccessful )
 739                  {
 740                     Int32 charCount = 0;
 741                     Boolean completed;
 742                     do
 743                     {
 744                        decoder.Convert( stream.Buffer, arrayIndex, stream.ReadBytesCount - arrayIndex, auxArray, 0, 2, 
 745                     } while ( ( charCount < 2 || !completed ) && await stream.TryReadMoreAsync( minChar ) );
 746
 747                     if ( charCount > 1 )
 748                     {
 749                        // Check for surrogate pair
 750                        if ( Char.IsHighSurrogate( auxArray[0] ) )
 751                        {
 752                           Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._lowSurrogate, (Int32) auxArray[1] );
 753                        }
 754                        else
 755                        {
 756                           // Unread peeked byte
 757                           stream.UnreadBytes( minChar );
 758                        }
 759                     }
 760                  }
 761
 762                  retVal = charReadSuccessful ? auxArray[0] : (Char?) null;
 763
 764               }
 765
 766               return retVal;
 767            }
 768            finally
 769            {
 770               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 771            }
 772         }
 773         else
 774         {
 775            throw BusyException();
 776         }
 777      }
 778
 779      /// <inheritdoc />
 780      public Boolean IsReadSuccessful( Char? readResult )
 781      {
 782         return readResult.HasValue;
 783      }

 1016   )

 1025      }

 01028   }

 1048   /// <summary>
 1049   /// Tries to read more items into the buffer of this <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}
 1050   /// </summary>
 1051   /// <param name="reader">This <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}"/>.</param>
 1052   /// <param name="amountToRead">The amount of items to read.</param>
 1053   /// <returns>A task which will tell how many items were actually read.</returns>
 1054   /// <exception cref="NullReferenceException">If this <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}
 1055   public static async ValueTask<Int32> TryReadMore<TValue>(
 1056      this MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader<TValue?, TValue> reader,
 1057      Int32 amountToRead
 1058      )
 1059      where TValue : struct
 1060   {
 01061      ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNullReference( reader );
 1062
 01063      var leftToRead = amountToRead;
 01064      while ( leftToRead > 0 && ( await reader.TryReadNextAsync() ).HasValue )
 1065      {
 01066         --leftToRead;
 1067      }
 1068
 01069      return amountToRead - leftToRead;
 01070   }
 1071
 1072   /// <summary>
 1073   /// Read more items into the buffer of this <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}"/>, or t
 1074   /// </summary>
 1075   /// <param name="reader">This <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}"/>.</param>
 1076   /// <param name="amountToRead">The amount of items to read.</param>
 1077   /// <returns>A task always returning <c>true</c>.</returns>
 1078   /// <exception cref="NullReferenceException">If this <see cref="MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader{TValue, TBufferItem}
 1079   /// <exception cref="EndOfStreamException">If not enough items could be read.</exception>
 1080   public static async ValueTask<Boolean> ReadMoreOrThrow<TValue>(
 1081      this MemorizingPotentiallyAsyncReader<TValue?, TValue> reader,
 1082      Int32 amountToRead
 1083      )
 1084      where TValue : struct
 1085   {
 01086      if ( await reader.TryReadMore( amountToRead ) != amountToRead )
 1087      {
 01088         throw new EndOfStreamException();
 1089      }
 1090
 01091      return true;

 320   internal class StreamReaderWithResizableBufferImpl : StreamReaderWithResizableBuffer
 321   {
 322      private const Int32 IDLE = 0;
 323      private const Int32 READING = 1;
 324      private const Int32 RESERVED_FOR_INNER_READER = 3;
 325      private const Int32 MANIPULATING_BUFFER = 4;
 326      private const Int32 WAITING_ON_INNER_REMAINING_READ = 5;
 327      private const Int32 READING_INNER_REMAINING = 6;
 328
 329      private readonly Stream _stream;
 330      private readonly ResizableArray<Byte> _buffer;
 331      private readonly Int32 _chunkSize;
 332
 333      protected Int32 _bytesInBufferUsedUp;
 334      protected Int32 _bytesInBuffer;
 335      private Int32 _state;
 336      private Int64 _innerStreamReadRemains;
 337
 338      public StreamReaderWithResizableBufferImpl(
 339         Stream stream,
 340         CancellationToken token,
 341         ResizableArray<Byte> buffer,
 342         Int32 chunkSize
 343         ) : this( stream, token, buffer, 0, chunkSize, true )
 344      {
 345      }
 346
 347      protected StreamReaderWithResizableBufferImpl(
 348         Stream stream,
 349         CancellationToken token,
 350         ResizableArray<Byte> buffer,
 351         Int32 bytesInBuffer,
 352         Int32 chunkSize,
 353         Boolean checkForStream
 354         )
 355      {
 356         if ( checkForStream )
 357         {
 358            ArgumentValidator.ValidateNotNull( nameof( stream ), stream );
 359         }
 360
 361
 362         this._stream = stream;
 363         this.CancellationToken = token;
 364         this._buffer = buffer ?? new ResizableArray<Byte>();
 365         this._chunkSize = Math.Max( 1, chunkSize );
 366         if ( buffer != null )
 367         {
 368            this._bytesInBuffer = Math.Max( this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, bytesInBuffer );
 369         }
 370      }
 371
 372      public Byte[] Buffer => this._buffer.Array;
 373
 374      public CancellationToken CancellationToken { get; }

 378      public void EraseReadBytesFromBuffer()
 379      {
 380         if ( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, MANIPULATING_BUFFER, IDLE ) == IDLE )
 381         {
 382            try
 383            {
 384               this.ForgetUsedBytes();
 385            }
 386            finally
 387            {
 388               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 389            }
 390         }
 391         else
 392         {
 393            throw BusyException();
 394         }
 395      }
 396
 397      public Int32 ReadBytesCount
 398      {

 402         }
 403      }

 405      public void EraseReadBufferSegment( Int32 firstDeletableByteIndex, Int32 count )
 406      {
 407         if ( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, MANIPULATING_BUFFER, IDLE ) == IDLE )
 408         {
 409            try
 410            {
 411               if ( firstDeletableByteIndex >= 0 && count > 0 && firstDeletableByteIndex + count <= this._bytesInBufferU
 412               {
 413                  this.Buffer.ShiftArraySegmentLeft( ref this._bytesInBuffer, firstDeletableByteIndex, count );
 414                  Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, this._bytesInBufferUsedUp - count );
 415               }
 416            }
 417            finally
 418            {
 419               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 420            }
 421         }
 422         else
 423         {
 424            throw BusyException();
 425         }
 426      }
 427
 428      public void UnreadBytes( Int32 amount )
 429      {
 430         if ( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, MANIPULATING_BUFFER, IDLE ) == IDLE )
 431         {
 432            try
 433            {
 434               if ( amount < 0 )
 435               {
 436                  amount = this._bytesInBufferUsedUp;
 437               }
 438
 439               if ( amount > 0 && amount <= this._bytesInBufferUsedUp )
 440               {
 441                  Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, this._bytesInBufferUsedUp - amount );
 442                  this.ReadCompletedSynchronously( -amount );
 443               }
 444            }
 445            finally
 446            {
 447               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 448            }
 449         }
 450
 451      }

 463      public InnerStreamReaderWithResizableBufferAndLimitedSize CreateWithLimitedSizeAndSharedBuffer( Int64 byteCount )
 464      {
 465         InnerStreamReaderWithResizableBufferAndLimitedSize retVal;
 466         if ( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, RESERVED_FOR_INNER_READER, IDLE ) == IDLE )
 467         {
 468            var resetState = true;
 469            try
 470            {
 471               if ( byteCount > 0 && ( byteCount = this.CheckByteCountForNewLimitedStream( byteCount ) ) > 0 )
 472               {
 473                  this.ForgetUsedBytes();
 474                  resetState = false;
 475                  var needsStream = byteCount > this._bytesInBuffer - this._bytesInBufferUsedUp;
 476                  retVal = new InnerStreamReaderWithResizableBufferAndLimitedSizeImpl(
 477                     needsStream ? this._stream : null,
 478                     this.CancellationToken,
 479                     this._buffer,
 480                     this._chunkSize,
 481                     byteCount,
 482                     this._bytesInBuffer,
 483                     this.OnInnerStreamDispose
 484                     );
 485
 486               }
 487               else
 488               {
 489                  retVal = new EmptyReader( this.CancellationToken );
 490               }
 491            }
 492            finally
 493            {
 494               if ( resetState )
 495               {
 496                  Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 497               }
 498            }
 499         }
 500         else
 501         {
 502            throw BusyException();
 503         }
 504
 505         return retVal;
 506      }
 507
 508      private async ValueTask<Boolean> PerformReadAsync(
 509         Int32 count,
 510         Boolean forgetUsedBytes
 511         )
 512      {
 513         await this.TryReadRemainsOfInnerStream();
 514
 515         var retVal = count > 0;
 516         if ( retVal )
 517         {
 518            if ( Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, READING, IDLE ) == IDLE )
 519            {
 520               try
 521               {
 522                  if ( forgetUsedBytes )
 523                  {
 524                     this.ForgetUsedBytes();
 525                  }
 526
 527                  count = this.CheckByteCountForBufferRead( count );
 528                  retVal = count > 0;
 529                  if ( retVal )
 530                  {
 531                     var newLimit = this._bytesInBufferUsedUp + count;
 532                     if ( newLimit <= this._bytesInBuffer )
 533                     {
 534                        // No need to read from stream
 535                        Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, newLimit );
 536                        this.ReadCompletedSynchronously( count );
 537                     }
 538                     else
 539                     {
 540                        // Calculate how much we really need to read
 541                        var amountToReadFromStream = Math.Max( newLimit - this._bytesInBuffer, this._chunkSize );
 542                        amountToReadFromStream = this.CheckByteCountForBufferRead( amountToReadFromStream );
 543                        retVal = amountToReadFromStream > 0 || this._bytesInBufferUsedUp < this._bytesInBuffer;
 544                        if ( retVal )
 545                        {
 546
 547                           if ( amountToReadFromStream > 0 )
 548                           {
 549                              // make sure buffer will have room
 550                              this._buffer.CurrentMaxCapacity = this._bytesInBuffer + amountToReadFromStream;
 551
 552                              // Perform read async
 553                              amountToReadFromStream = await this._stream.TryReadSpecificAmountAsync( this.Buffer, this.
 554                              Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBuffer, this._bytesInBuffer + amountToReadFromStrea
 555                           }
 556
 557                           count = Math.Min( count, this._bytesInBuffer - this._bytesInBufferUsedUp );
 558                           retVal = count > 0;
 559                           if ( retVal )
 560                           {
 561                              Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, this._bytesInBufferUsedUp + count );
 562
 563                              if ( amountToReadFromStream > 0 )
 564                              {
 565                                 this.ReadCompletedAsynchronously( count, amountToReadFromStream );
 566                              }
 567                              else
 568                              {
 569                                 this.ReadCompletedSynchronously( count );
 570                              }
 571                           }
 572                        }
 573                     }
 574                  }
 575               }
 576               finally
 577               {
 578                  Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 579               }
 580            }
 581            else
 582            {
 583               throw BusyException();
 584            }
 585         }
 586
 587         return retVal;
 588      }
 589
 590      private void ForgetUsedBytes()
 591      {
 592         if ( this._bytesInBufferUsedUp > 0 && this._bytesInBufferUsedUp <= this._bytesInBuffer )
 593         {
 594            this._buffer.Array.ShiftArraySegmentLeft( ref this._bytesInBuffer, 0, this._bytesInBufferUsedUp );
 595            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, 0 );
 596         }
 597      }
 598
 599      private async ValueTask<Boolean> TryReadRemainsOfInnerStream()
 600      {
 601         Int32 prevState;
 602         var retVal = ( prevState = Interlocked.CompareExchange( ref this._state, READING_INNER_REMAINING, WAITING_ON_IN
 603         if ( retVal )
 604         {
 605            try
 606            {
 607               var curRead = Interlocked.Read( ref this._innerStreamReadRemains );
 608               if ( curRead > this._buffer.CurrentMaxCapacity )
 609               {
 610                  this._buffer.CurrentMaxCapacity = Min( curRead, this._chunkSize );
 611               }
 612               var bytesRemaining = curRead;
 613               Int32 lastReadCount;
 614               do
 615               {
 616                  lastReadCount = await this._stream.TryReadSpecificAmountAsync( this.Buffer, 0, Min( curRead, this._chu
 617                  curRead -= lastReadCount;
 618               } while ( lastReadCount > 0 && curRead > 0 );
 619
 620               this.ReadCompletedAsynchronously( 0, Interlocked.Read( ref this._innerStreamReadRemains ) );
 621               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._innerStreamReadRemains, 0 );
 622               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, 0 );
 623               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBuffer, 0 );
 624            }
 625            finally
 626            {
 627               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 628            }
 629         }
 630         else if ( prevState == READING_INNER_REMAINING )
 631         {
 632            throw BusyException();
 633         }
 634
 635         return retVal;
 636      }
 637
 638      protected virtual Int64 CheckByteCountForNewLimitedStream( Int64 byteCount )
 639      {
 640         return byteCount;
 641      }
 642
 643      protected virtual void ReadCompletedSynchronously( Int64 count )
 644      {
 645         // Do nothing
 646      }
 647
 648      protected virtual Int32 CheckByteCountForBufferRead( Int32 givenCount )
 649      {
 650         return givenCount;
 651      }
 652
 653      protected virtual void ReadCompletedAsynchronously( Int64 count, Int64 streamReadCount )
 654      {
 655         // Do nothing
 656      }
 657
 658      protected void OnInnerStreamDispose(
 659         Int64 innerStreamSize,
 660         Int64 bytesLeft,
 661         Int64 initialStreamBytesLeftToRead,
 662         Int64 streamBytesLeftToRead,
 663         Int32 bytesInBufferUsedUp,
 664         Int32 bytesInBufferTotal
 665         )
 666      {
 667         System.Diagnostics.Debug.Assert( streamBytesLeftToRead <= bytesLeft );
 668
 669         var innerReaderNeededStream = innerStreamSize > this._bytesInBuffer - this._bytesInBufferUsedUp;
 670         if ( streamBytesLeftToRead <= 0 )
 671         {
 672            // No asynchrony will be needed, just update variables
 673            if ( innerReaderNeededStream )
 674            {
 675               // This only happens when inner stream read from System.IO.Stream at least once
 676               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBuffer, bytesInBufferTotal );
 677               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, bytesInBufferUsedUp + (Int32) bytesLeft );
 678            }
 679            else
 680            {
 681               Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._bytesInBufferUsedUp, this._bytesInBufferUsedUp + (Int32) innerStreamSize 
 682            }
 683
 684            this.ReadCompletedAsynchronously( innerStreamSize, initialStreamBytesLeftToRead );
 685
 686            // Then forget the bytes
 687            this.ForgetUsedBytes();
 688
 689            // Reset our state
 690            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, IDLE );
 691         }
 692         else
 693         {
 694            // We must read the remaining stream bytes on next call to TryRead/TryReadMore
 695            this.ReadCompletedSynchronously( bytesLeft );
 696
 697            // Set up state to be waiting for async read
 698            Interlocked.Exchange( ref this._state, WAITING_ON_INNER_REMAINING_READ );
 699         }
 700      }
 701
 702      private static InvalidOperationException BusyException()
 703      {
 704         return new InvalidOperationException( "This buffer is not useable right now." );
 705      }
 706
 707      internal static Int32 Min( Int64 i64, Int32 i32 )
 708      {
 709         return i64 < i32 ? (Int32) i64 : i32;
 710      }
 711   }

 845   internal class StreamWriterWithResizableBufferImpl : StreamWriterWithResizableBuffer
 846   {
 847      private const Int32 IDLE = 0;
 848      private const Int32 OPERATING_STREAM = 1;
 849      private const Int32 OPERATING_SUB_STREAM = 2;
 850
 851      private readonly Stream _stream;
 852      private readonly ResizableArray<Byte> _buffer;
 853
 854      protected Int32 _appendedByteCount;
 855      private Int32 _state;
 856
 857      public StreamWriterWithResizableBufferImpl(
 858         Stream stream,
 859         CancellationToken token,
 860         ResizableArray<Byte> buffer
 861         )
 862      {
 863         this._stream = stream;
 864         this.CancellationToken = token;
 865         this._buffer = buffer ?? new ResizableArray<Byte>();
 866      }
